This is a case study project for reactive programming with kafka streams.
The current README file is just my working notes. 
Project related  README will be submitted once the project is completed.

public vs private keys
public key is a "padlock" - can be safely distributed to number of remote machine
provite key is a "KEY" you use to open "padlock" (public key) - is kept privately on local compute only


https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/streams/
